{"title": "Tarzan and the Golden Lion", "description": "Tarzan's amazing ability to establish kinship with some of the most dangerous animals in the jungle serves him well in this exciting story of his adventures with the Golden Lion, Jad-bal-ja, when the great and lordly animal becomes his ally and protector.\nTarzan learns from the High Priestess, La, of a country north of Opar which is held in dread by the Oparians. It is peopled by a strange race of gorilla-men with the intelligence of humans and the strength of gorillas. From time to time they attack Opar, carrying off prisoners for use as slaves in the jewel-studded Temple where they worship a great black-maned lion. \nAccompanied by the faithful Jad-bal-ja, Tarzan invades the dread country in an attempt to win freedom for the hundreds of people held in slavery there... - Summary by Edgar Rice Burroughs\n<br /><br />\nProof-listeners: softstepgd and Mark Nelson", "duration": 23428, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "698", "name": "Edgar Rice Burroughs"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/tarzan_golden_lion_1905_librivox/tarzanandthegoldenlion_1905.jpg", "copyright_year": "1923", "genres": ["Action & Adventure Fiction", "Nature & Animal Fiction", "Published 1900 onward"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Joshua Herring"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Joshua Herring"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Golden Lion", "readers": [13034], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/tarzan_golden_lion_1905_librivox/tarzanandthegoldenlion_01_burroughs_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1078}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Training of Jad-bal-ja", "readers": [13034], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/tarzan_golden_lion_1905_librivox/tarzanandthegoldenlion_02_burroughs_64kb.mp3", "duration": 687}, {"section": 3, "title": "A Meeting of Mystery", "readers": [13034], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/tarzan_golden_lion_1905_libriv